text.section:
"Apartment unit" means any space, in a residential building, that is enclosed and self-contained and has a sanitary environment, if the space includes:
2 or more rooms;
A direct exit to a thoroughfare or to a common element leading to a thoroughfare;
Facilities for living, sleeping, and eating; and
At least the following facilities for cooking:
Storage space for food and utensils;
A refrigerator;
A cook top; and
Adequate electrical capacity and outlets for small appliances.

section.section:
"Domiciliary care" includes:
Shelter;
Housekeeping services;
Board;
Facilities and resources for daily living; and
Personal surveillance or direction in the activities of daily living.

text.section:
"Limited service hospital" means a health care facility that:
Is licensed as a hospital on or after January 1, 1999;
Changes the type or scope of health care services offered by eliminating the facility's capability to admit or retain patients for overnight hospitalization;
Retains an emergency or urgent care center; and
Complies with the regulations adopted by the Secretary under § 19-307.1 of this subtitle.

section.section:
"Personal care" includes:
Help in walking;
Help in getting in and out of bed;
Help in bathing;
Help in dressing;
Help in feeding; and
General supervision and help in daily living.
